’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry de Waleton was born on 1 May 1151, in Halewood, Lancashire, England, his father, Gilbert De Waleton, was 29 and his mother, Mrs. Gilbert de Waleton, was 27. He married Juliana of Halewood. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. He died on 9 September 1199, in Halewood, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 48."},"et":{"1 May 1151–9 September 1199":"1. mai 1151–9. september 1199","1145–1235":"1145–1235","1151–1199":"1151–1199","1155–1181":"1155–1181","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1181–1230":"1181–1230","–1246":"–1246","–1262":"–1262","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1122–1205":"1122–1205","1124–1160":"1124–1160","1190":"1190","1 May 1151":"1. mai 1151","about 1180":"umbes 1180","1 November 1181":"1. november 1181","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1151":"1151","1160":"1160","1181":"1181","1180":"1180","1205":"1205","1 August 1181":"1. august 1181","9 September 1199":"9. september 1199","1246":"1246","1235":"1235","1124":"1124","1200":"1200","1145":"1145","1122":"1122","1155":"1155","1199":"1199","Walton-le-Dale, Lancashire, England":"Walton-le-Dale, Lancashire, England","Halewood, Lancashire, England":"Halewood, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Walton on the Hill, Lancashire, England":"Walton on the Hill, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1 May 1151–9 September 1199":"1. toukokuuta 1151–9. syyskuuta 1199","1145–1235":"1145–1235","1151–1199":"1151–1199","1155–1181":"1155–1181","1180–Male":